<HL> Agassiz to Buy Stake
Of 59% in SherrGold
From Sherritt Gordon</HL>
<DD> 06/25/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> T.AGZ T.SE NEM
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN>
<DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Agassiz Resources Ltd. said it agreed to acquire Sherritt Gordon Mines Ltd.'s 59% interest in SherrGold Inc. and certain other mining assets of Sherritt. 

   Terms of the transaction weren't disclosed. 

   SherrGold operates the MacLellan gold mine at Lynn Lake, Manitoba. 
Based on SherrGold's closing price on the Toronto Stock Exchange yesterday, the Sherritt stake is valued at about 36.8 million Canadian dollars ($27.6 million). 

   Agassiz is an oil and gas and mining concern. 
Agassiz said that after the transaction closes in mid-July, it plans to exchange its 7% gross gold and silver royalty in the MacLellan mine for additional common shares of SherrGold. 
Details of the exchange weren't announced. 

   Sherritt said the sale of its SherrGold stake is in line with its previously announced plans to sell certain assets and strengthen its financial position. 
Sherritt is a mining, metal refining and fabricating, and fertilizer concern 35%-owned by Newmont Mining Corp., New York. 

